Brown marmorated stink bug (BMSB), Halyomorpha halys (Stål) (Hemiptera: 
Pentatomidae), is a pest of concern that must be controlled for market access of 
host material and regulated articles to certain countries. This work outlines a 
rearing system for BMSB on live cowpea plants, Vigna unguiculata (L.) Walp. 
(Fabales: Fabaceae), including methods to induce adults to both enter and exit 
diapause. This scalable system affords continuous access to >600 specimens per 
week of each life stage and/or age group, which is particularly advantageous 
when developing treatment efficacy data.

